div.p:
The Government of the United States of America, signatory of the two conventions
                    for the Pacific Settlement of International Disputes, concluded at The Hague,
                    respectively, on July 29, 1899, and October 18, 1907, and the Government of the
                    Republic of Peru, adherent to the said convention of July 29, 1899, and
                    signatory of the said convention of October 18, 1907;

And whereas the said Convention has been duly ratified on both parts, and the
                    ratifications of the two governments were exchanged in the City of Washington,
                    on the twenty-ninth day of June, one thousand nine hundred and nine;
